fields.title: Creating%20a%20Chrome%20extension%20with%20React%20and%20TypeScript
fields.content: Creating a Chrome extension with React and TypeScript August 12, 2021 10 min read See how LogRocket's AI-powered error tracking works no signup required. with extensions becoming increasingly complex, developers created solutions that enabled pre-existing tools to scale and adapt. frameworks like React, for example, improve web development and are even used — instead of vanilla JavaScript — for building web extensions.

fields.title: Dijkstra%27s%20algorithm
fields.content: DYKE-strz is an algorithm for finding the shortest paths between nodes in a weighted graph. it was conceived by computer scientist Edsger W. Dijkstra in 1956 and published three years later. the algorithm can also be used for finding the shortest paths from a single node to a single destination node.

fields.content: this week's Newsweek Pet of the Week winner is petie, a 6-year-old rescue dog. petie likes to suckle on blankets at night in order to fall asleep. owner: "i'm pretty sure he has some bird dog in him and maybe a little lab" if you want your pet to be part of next week's line-up, follow the instructions at the end of this article to find out how.

fields.title: Golden%20Retriever%20Dog%20Breed%20Facts%20%26%20Information
fields.content: golden retrievers were originally bred to retrieve fowl for hunters, but now they’re happy in many other roles, too, from playing endless fetch with their owners to working as service dogs. their long floppy ears combine with their playful personality to create the look of an eternal puppy.

fields.title: Golden%20Years
fields.content: some vets think golden retrievers are dying younger than they used to. golden retrievers are one of the most popular breeds in the country. a consensus among veterinarians that golden retrievers have the highest rates of cancer of any dog breed. the answer could change how we think about dogs for good, experts say.

fields.title: TARJAN%E2%80%99S%20ALGORITHM%20FOR%20STRONGLY%20CONNECTED%20COMPONENTS
fields.content: Tarjan Low-link value is the smallest node ID reachable from a node when doing a depth-first search (DFS), including itself. the low-link value of a node is the smallest node ID reachable from that node when doing a depth-first search (DFS). low-link values are highly dependent on the traversal order of the DFS, which is effectively random.

fields.title: Can%20you%20explain%20Bleichenbacher%27s%20CCA%20attack%20on%20PKCS%231%20v1.5%3F
fields.content: Bleichenbacher's CCA attack on PKCS#1 v1.5. is a base to many versions of attacks in the area. the attack works if there is some system, somewhere, which can tell, given a sequence of bytes of the length of an encrypted message, whether decryption would yield something which has the proper padding format or not.

fields.content: Lionel Messi has won the men's ballon d'or for an eighth time. the 36-year-old helped his country win the world cup in Qatar last year. he was recognised at the ceremony in Paris after helping his country win the world cup in qatar last year.
